        "prose": "Food waste is 60-80% water. Evaporating water requires overcoming the latent heat of vaporization—2,260 kJ/kg, which translates to a theoretical minimum of 627 kWh/ton just for the phase change. Real systems lose 30-50% additional energy to exhaust, radiation, and inefficient heat transfer. At small scale (500 lb/day), surface-to-volume ratios make heat retention even worse. The physics creates a floor that no amount of insulation or control optimization can break through if evaporation is the only water removal mechanism."
